# AdultSwim Android App

## Getting Started

This software requires API 15 and above. 

* Get the source code and install/deploy it using Eclipse.

* Install [Maven](http://maven.apache.org/) by installing the following eclipse plugins

  http://download.eclipse.org/technology/m2e/releases
  http://rgladwell.github.com/m2e-android/updates/

* In terminal, change the directory to the folder containing the source code and run the commands below:
  
  mvn install:install-file -Dfile=./src/lib/movideo_android_sdk-1.0.7.jar -DgroupId=com.movideo -DartifactId=movideo -Dversion=1.0.7 -Dpackaging=jar
  mvn install:install-file -Dfile=./src/lib/TestFlightLib.jar -DgroupId=com.testflight -DartifactId=testflight -Dversion=1.0 -Dpackaging=jar
  mvn install:install-file -Dfile=./src/lib/android-support-v4.jar -DgroupId=com.android -DartifactId=support-v4 -Dversion=r18 -Dpackaging=jar
  mvn install:install-file -Dfile=./src/lib/GoogleAdMobAdsSdk-6.4.1.jar -DgroupId=com.google -DartifactId=doubleclick -Dversion=6.4.1 -Dpackaging=jar
  mvn install:install-file -Dfile=./src/lib/libGoogleAnalyticsServices.jar -DgroupId=com.google -DartifactId=analytics -Dversion=3 -Dpackaging=jar
  mvn install


* Import project as an existing maven project.

* Open pom.xml and find <path> under<configuration><sdk>,change path location to point your android sdk library.

* Right Click the project and select Maven-> Update Project.

## Target Devices 

Android Phone, Tablet (4.0.3 and above)

## External Dependecies

This project uses [Maven](http://maven.apache.org/) as the libray dependencies manager.

* Movideo SDK(1.0.7)
* RoboSpice (1.4.5)
* RoboElectric (2.1.1)
* Junit (4.2.2)
* UrlImageViewHelper (1.0.4)
* DoubleClickSDK (6.4.1)
* GoogleAnalytics SDK (3)
* Logback-android (1.0.10-2)
* Testflight(1.0)
